CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1963, pg. 1, reads: "Will Demonstrations Be Staged Here? - Members of Pittsburgh's newly formed Unity Committee have selected several targets around Pittsburgh as sites of possible mass demonstrations. Four of them are shown here.  Left to right: Duquesne Light Co. on Sixth Ave... - Harris Photos
TitMainTitle: Duquesne Light Company building at intersection of Sixth Avenue and William Penn Place, seen from Mellon Square, Downtown
